<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>
<p>A <rs type="material" key="marmor">white marble</rs> <rs type="objectType">column</rs> fluted above and smooth below. '<foreign lang="de">Höhe: <measure dim="height">154</measure>, Breite: <measure dim="width">220</measure>.</foreign>'.</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="text">
<head>Description of Text</head>
<p>Inscribed on the smooth surface, below the fluting.</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Description of Letters</head>
<p><measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.085</measure>; irregular, somewhat elongated; abbreviations: scroll in l.1, <foreign lang="grc">Ρ</foreign> above line in l. 3.</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p><date exact="none" cert="low" notBefore="0368" notAfter="0400">Later fourth century</date> (<rs type="criteria">titulature</rs>, <rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>).</p>
</div>

<div n="text" lang="grc" type="edition">
<head lang="en">Edition</head>
<ab><lb n="1"/><persName type="aphrodisian" key="pelagius" full="yes"><name type=" " reg="Φλάβιος"><expan><abbr>Φλ<orig><g type="scroll"/></orig></abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">αουίου</supplied></expan></name>  <name type=" " reg="Πελάγιος">Πελαγίου</name> <lb n="2"/><name reg="Ἰωάννης">Ἰωάννου</name></persName> <lb n="3"/><w lemma="ὁ">τοῦ</w> <rs type="dignity" key="clarissimus"><w lemma="λαμπρός"><expan><abbr>λαμπ<hi rend="superscript">ρ</hi></abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">οτάτου</supplied></expan></w></rs> <lb n="4"/><rs type="official-secul" key="praeses"><w lemma="ἡγεμών">ἡγεμόνος</w></rs>
</ab>
</div>

<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p><supplied cert="low" reason="subaudible">Gift of</supplied> Flavius Pelagius Ioannes, <term lang="la">clarissimus praeses</term>.</p>
</div>

<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>For Fl. Pelagius Ioannes see discussion at <xref type="eAla-text" n="III.32">III.32</xref>.</p>
</div>

<div type="history" n="locations"><head>Locations</head><p>Found: <rs type="found"><rs type="monuList">North Agora</rs>; south portico on the eighth column (counted from the east) '<foreign lang="de">der Rest der 8. Säule</foreign>' (Kubitschek). .</rs>. Original location: <rs type="origLocation">Findspot</rs>. Last recorded location: <rs type="lastLocation">This remnant has now disappeared, probably into the nearby water channel, which is lined with column fragments</rs>. </p></div>



